Project Goal:
Build a modern, responsive Nigerian hotel booking website with full booking functionality, powered by React + Firebase. The site should emphasize local culture, seamless UX, and reliable payments.

Core Stack:

Frontend: React + Vite

Styling: TailwindCSS

Animations: framer-motion / anime.js

Backend & Services: Firebase (Auth, Firestore, Storage, Hosting, Functions if needed)

Payments: Paystack or Flutterwave (NGN)

Features & Pages
1. Authentication (Firebase Auth)

Email/password login & signup.

Social login: Google (optional).

Role-based auth: Admin (hotel owners) and Users (guests).

2. Homepage

Nigerian hotel/resort hero banner with CTA (“Book Now”).

Animated carousel of top hotels.

Testimonials stored in Firestore.

Newsletter subscription (Firestore collection).

3. Hotels/Rooms Listing (Firestore)

Data pulled from Firestore “hotels” collection.

Filtering: location (Lagos, Abuja, Port Harcourt), price range, rating.

Search functionality.

Hotel cards with hover animations.

4. Single Hotel Page

Data dynamically loaded from Firestore (/hotels/{hotelId}).

Photo gallery (images stored in Firebase Storage).

Room details, amenities, availability calendar.

Booking button → opens booking flow.

5. Booking Flow (Firestore + Paystack/Flutterwave)

Select dates & room type.

Enter guest details.

Process payment via Paystack/Flutterwave.

On success, booking saved in Firestore (/bookings/{bookingId}).

Confirmation page with animated checkmark.

6. Admin Dashboard

Add/edit/delete hotels & rooms (CRUD in Firestore).

Upload hotel images to Firebase Storage.

View bookings & payments.

7. Contact Page

Contact form → saves messages to Firestore.

Phone/WhatsApp links.

Embedded Google Maps (hotel location).

Firebase Structure (example)

users → {uid, name, email, role}

hotels → {id, name, city, price, rating, images[], description, amenities[]}

bookings → {id, userId, hotelId, checkIn, checkOut, guests, paymentStatus}

messages → {id, userId, subject, message}

Technical Notes

Use Firestore for real-time hotel availability updates.

Store hotel photos in Firebase Storage.

Protect admin routes with Firebase Auth + role checks.

Deploy frontend via Firebase Hosting.

(Optional) Use Firebase Functions for payment webhook handling (Paystack/Flutterwave).